  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessing the Health Literacy and Health Communication Needs of Syrian Refugees in Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As part of the efforts to assess the health needs of Syrian refugees, IOM is delivering a non-research survey on the health literacy level and health communication needs among the Syrian refugees in seven select provinces of Turkey&#x2014;Istanbul, Gaziantep, Sanliurfa, Bursa, Mersin, Izmir, and Konya. IOM will implement this project through a research methodology focusing on three related objectives: (1) assessing and determining the current level of health literacy among Syrian refugees; (2) determining health information needs and access to health information and consumption habits of communication channels; and (3) developing recommendations for improving health literacy and health communication. In addition, IOM&#x2019;s Migrants&#x2019; Presence Monitoring (MPM) is working jointly with its Health experts to design and assess the survey and report which will include key recommendations for health actors in Turkey.</narrative>
  </description>
